  "texts": [
    "Our results from Experiment 4 also shows that BERT-based LLMs performed the best when fine-tuned on ensembled data from all evaluation datasets.",
    "This, however, requires a larger amount of annotated data for fine-tuning.",
    "A possible workaround is to use the zero-shot LLMs to generate synthetic data with labels and use the generated data to augment the fine-tuning dataset with BERT-based models.",
    "Though zero or few-shot LLMs themselves may not be able to produce accurate sentiment labels, their superior ability to generate human-like texts can be leveraged in augmenting annotated data to improve the performance on downstream tasks.",
    "Despite the promising performance and the ease of use of the zero-shot LLMs on health-related social media data, we also note challenges and issues that researchers should be aware of when using these LLMs."
  ],
